The paper deals with algorithms and analysis for graph problems, specifically the minimum $k$-cut problem. This falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Computational Geometry" (cs.CG). The paper also involves the analysis of an LP relaxation, which falls under "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM) and "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of bounds and approximations, which falls under "Game Theory" (cs.GT).
